<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05587</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTING A POVERTY-ALLEVIATION MEASURE TO UPLIFT  THE MOST CRITICALLY-SITUATED MUNICIPALITIES IN THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : “ Oplan Tanggal Hirap Act ”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to ensure that the poorest municipalities will be able to avail of basic social services of the government and improved their quality of life; Mandates therefore the National Anti-Poverty Commission with the DSWD to conduct a study to determine the three most critically situated municipalities in every province; Provides for the standards to be used in determining such areas to be enrolled under the Program which may include per capita income, infant mortality rate, poverty-incidence, unemployment rate, etc.; 
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ZUBIRI, MANUEL F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-05-08</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (002 2017-07-25)</td><td>2. Bulut-Begtang (017 2017-09-04)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON POVERTY ALLEVIATION ON 2017-05-15</td></tr></table>